A motorist and his girlfriend were ejected from the vehicle they were travelling in after the car slammed into a tree, on Oakford Road in Verulam, on Sunday. Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) responded to the call for assistance and upon arrival, reaction officers found that the driver of a silver VW Polo, 28, sustained extensive injuries.
“Advanced Life Support (ALS) paramedics were called out to an accident scene to render urgent medical assistance to the critically injured man. Both the driver and his girlfriend were ejected several metres from the point of impact. The woman suffered moderate injuries. “The vehicle engine was found lying a short distance from the vehicle after it became dislodged during the crash,” said Rusa boss, Prem Balram.